<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-284-087 </DOCNO><DOCID>06 875 545</DOCID><JOURNAL>Patricia Seybold's Office Computing Report  July 1988 v11 n7p22(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A PC integrated office suite. (WordPerfect Corp announcesWordPerfect Office for LANs)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Marshak, David S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>WordPerfect Corp has released the WordPerfect Office for PCNetworks, which is the first attempt at a LAN-based integratedoffice environment by a major PC software vendor.andP;  The programretails for $495 for the file server and $150 for each workstationand runs on DOS 3.1 PC LANs.andP;  The system offers programs such asWordPerfect, PlanPerfect, and DataPerfect, along with OfficeModules that are generally found only in host-based integratedoffice systems.andP;  These include mail, notebook, calendar, andscheduler modules.andP;  WordPerfect Corp plans to introduce the systemonto other targeted platforms such as Unix, VMS, Macintosh, andOS-2, and hopes that its large, loyal base of word processingusers will provide an initial launch point for this system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   WordPerfect Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   WordPerfect Office (Office automation software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     MicrocomputersLocal Area NetworksProduct IntroductionWord Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>